SerializerControllerResponse <pre><code>class BlogSerializer extends Serializer&lt;Blog&gt; {
    BlogSerializer(super.data);

    @override
    Map&lt;String, dynamic&gt; convert(Blog m) {
        return {
            'uid': m.id,
            'title_en' : m.title,
        };
    }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>class BlogController {
    getAllBlogs(DoxRequest req) async {
        List&lt;Blog&gt; blogs = await Blog().all();

        /// you can pass as list of data
        return BlogSerializer(blogs);
    }

    findBlog(DoxRequest req, id) async {
        Blog blog = await Blog().find(id);

        /// or you can also pass as single data
        return BlogSerializer(blog);
    }
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>{
    "uid" : "1",
    "title_en": "This is title"
}
</code></pre> <p>Info</p> <p>You can pass as list of data or single data into the serializer. Just make sure that you have injected your model type in serializer <code>Serializer&lt;Blog&gt;</code>.</p>

